org.linqs.psl.database.rdbms.driver

Interface DatabaseDriver

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    H2DatabaseDriver, PostgreSQLDriver

    public interface DatabaseDriver
    An interface to a specific RDBMS backend. All connections from drivers should be from thread-safe connection pools.

    • Method Detail

      • close

        void close()
        Close out any outstanding connections and cleanup.

      • getConnection

        Connection getConnection()
        Returns a connection to the database. Database drivers are expected to fully connect at instantiation (i.e. in the constructor). Implementation are expected to use connection pools. The connections retutned from this methods should be safe to close() without significant performance impact.
        Returns:
        the connection to the database, as specified in the DatabaseDriver constructor

      • supportsBulkCopy

        boolean supportsBulkCopy()
        Returns whether the underline database supports bulk copying operations.

              String delimiter,
              boolean hasTruth,
              PredicateInfo predicateInfo,
              Partition partition)
        Perform a bulk copy operation to load the file directly into the database. May not be supported by all backends.

      • getUpsert

        String getUpsert(String tableName,
                 String[] columns,
                 String[] keyColumns)
        Get the SQL for an upsert (merge) on the specified table and columns. An "upsert" updates existing records and inserts where there is no record. Most RDBMSs support some for of upsert, but the syntax is inconsistent. The parameters for the statement should the the specified columns in order. Some databases (like H2) require knowing the key columns we need to use.

      • finalizeCreateTable

        String finalizeCreateTable(com.healthmarketscience.sqlbuilder.CreateTableQuery createTable)
        Gives the driver a chance to perform any final manipulations to the CREATE TABLE statement.

      • getStringAggregate

        String getStringAggregate(String columnName,
                          String delimiter,
                          boolean distinct)
        Get a string aggregating expression (one that would appear in the SELECT clause of a grouping query. Postgres uses STRING_AGG and H2 use GROUP_CONCAT.

      • getTableStats

        TableStats getTableStats(PredicateInfo predicate)
        Get some statistics for a table.

      • updateDBStats

        void updateDBStats()
        Make sure that all the database-level stats are up-to-date. Is generally called after insertion and indexing.

      • updateTableStats

        void updateTableStats(PredicateInfo predicate)
        Make sure that all the table statistics are up-to-date. Is generally called after insertion and indexing.
